A \subset B \subset X
\mbox{dist}(x,B) \le \mbox{dist}(x,A)
\mbox{dist}(x,B) > \mbox{dist}(x,A)
(\forall a \in A)(\forall b \in B) \quad d(x,b)>d(x,a)
d(x,b) < d(x,a) + d(a,b)
(\forall a \in A)(\forall b \in B) \quad d(a,b)>0
(\forall a \in A)(\forall b \in B) \quad a \neq b
a \in A
a=b
b \in B
 \mbox{dist}(x,B)=\inf\{\mbox{dist}(x,b):\ b\in B\}\leq \inf\{\mbox{dist}(x,b):\ b\in A\}=\mbox{dist}(x,A). 
